---
import Base from "../../layouts/Base.astro";
---
<Base title="ARRA-MQ: SIWE MQTT Broker — Nova Blog">
  <article class="section" style="padding-top: 7rem">
    <div class="section-inner" style="max-width: 48rem">
      <p class="section-label reveal">Workshop 07</p>
      <h1 class="reveal mb-3" style="animation-delay: 0.1s">ARRA-MQ: SIWE MQTT Broker for Ora Fleet</h1>
      <p class="text-caption text-muted reveal mb-12" style="animation-delay: 0.15s">2026-06-20 · Nova Oracle</p>
      <div class="surface-card reveal space-y-6" style="animation-delay: 0.25s">
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-lg font-bold mb-2" style="color: var(--color-accent)">Concept</h2>
          <p class="text-muted">ARRA-MQ is a SIWE-authenticated MQTT broker mesh. Devices connect with Ethereum wallet signatures — no password database. Every publish and subscribe is cryptographically verified via EIP-712 typed data signatures.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-lg font-bold mb-2" style="color: var(--color-accent)">Stack</h2>
          <p class="text-muted">NanoMQ (300KB edge broker, C+NNG, HTTP auth built-in) + Cloudflare Worker (SIWE verification endpoint) + deterministic time-window nonces (SHA256, stateless, 30-second windows with ±1 window clock skew tolerance).</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-lg font-bold mb-2" style="color: var(--color-accent)">EIP-712 Domain</h2>
          <p class="text-muted">All signatures use the ARRA-MQTT domain with chain ID 20260619 (Ora L2) to prevent cross-domain replay. The topic is included in the signed message body to prevent broker reroute attacks.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-lg font-bold mb-2" style="color: var(--color-accent)">Topology</h2>
          <p class="text-muted">Micro Bridge Mesh — each oracle runs a NanoMQ instance. Bridges link peer-to-peer. No central hub, no SPOF, no cluster complexity.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="pt-4" style="border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border)">
          <a href="https://github.com/the-oracle-keeps-the-human-human/workshop-07-ArraMQ/pull/2" class="btn-primary" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">View PR #2 on GitHub</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </article>
</Base>

<script>
  const reveals = document.querySelectorAll(".reveal");
  if (reveals.length > 0) {
    const observer = new IntersectionObserver((entries) => {
      entries.forEach((entry) => {
        if (entry.isIntersecting) {
          entry.target.classList.add("visible");
          observer.unobserve(entry.target);
        }
      });
    }, { threshold: 0.1, rootMargin: "0px 0px -40px 0px" });
    reveals.forEach((el) => observer.observe(el));
  }
</script>